The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the problem of blur detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of multiscale transforms, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of gradient magnitudes, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics). The proposed approach involves the computation of blur detection maps, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed approach against state-of-the-art methods, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
